Last updated: November 18, 2024
Overview
This privacy policy applies to the DriveNow Driving Cancellations Ireland app created by Simon Jones as a Commercial service. This service is intended for use "AS IS".
Information Collection and Use
The Application collects only:
Device tokens for push notifications
User preferences (selected test centers, days, and times)
Purchase status through Apple's App Store
No personally identifiable information is collected.
Third Party Services
The Application uses only:
Firebase Cloud Messaging for push notifications
Apple's StoreKit for in-app purchases
Data Usage
Your preferences are used solely to send notifications about test cancellation availability. All purchase transactions are handled securely by Apple.
Children's Privacy
The Application does not knowingly collect any personal information from children under 13. Users must be at least 16 years old to consent to the processing of their information.
Data Deletion
You can delete all your preferences by uninstalling the app or disabling notifications. Purchase records are maintained by Apple according to their policies.
Data Collection from RSA
This app collects and displays test center availability data from the RSA (Road Safety Authority) website through an automated process that requires authentication. The data shown is the same information that is available to authenticated users on the RSA website. We do not store or modify the original RSA data.
Changes to Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Users will be notified of any changes by updating this page.
Contact
For privacy concerns, contact us at: maindrivenow@gmail.com